Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

- Total Liabilities at the end date (2024-01-29) = Total Current Liabilities = $3,054,996.05
- Total Assets at the end date (2024-01-29) = $14,879,933.86

Now I can calculate the ratio:
Debt to Asset Ratio = $3,054,996.05 / $14,879,933.86 = 0.2053 â‰ˆ 0.21

Rounding to two decimal places, the Debt to Asset Ratio is 0.21.
